In the open equares, in the coffeehouses, upon the streets, in the barracks, everywhere, one sees little circles, with six radii equally distant from each other, scratched in stone. In the Basilica J ulia it is usually a circle with eight radii. The decoratione at the ends of the diameters, which look like little hats for the stones, are, with- out doubt, for the game itself. Each of the two players receives three pieces of different shape or color. These are placed alter- nately at first, then pushed farther along the lines.
